{"word":"ἕδρανον","slug":"ἕδρανον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἕδρανον</b></el> <el>(ἕδρᾰνον, ου, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> form of <a href='S:ἕδρα'><el>ἕδρα</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a seat, abode</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a stay, support</i>, of an anchor, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}